  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project is studying the role of the therapeutic alliance between the therapist and
      patient in the outpatient treatment of persons with alcohol use disorders.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This project is studying the role of the therapeutic alliance between the therapist and
      patient in the outpatient treatment of persons with alcohol use disorders. Alliances are
      assessed over the course of treatment and will be reviewed in the context of posttreatment
      functioning.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
